bg: Project Information
Getting Over It: Multiplayer Edition
Modification of Griffpatch's Getting Over It Scratch remake
Mod created by Ezlambry
Getting Over It originally created by Bennett Foddy
Game version: 1.4
Mod version: 4.1
- = - RULES - = -
When playing Getting Over It: Multiplayer Edition you are
expected to follow the Scratch Community Guidelines.
Additionally, manually changing Cloud Data variables using
external programs in order to display innappropriate content
will be reported to the Scratch Team.
- = - CONTROLS - = -
H - Change Hat
T - Chat
G - Toggle if player can get pushed
V - Change name display mode
Space (when pressing New Game) - Start in Spectator Mode
- = - CREDITS - = -
Griffpatch - Cloud decoding and encoding scripts
Griffpatch - Voice acting
publicdomainvectors.org - Couch image in Multiplayer Hangout
E's Jammy Jams - You Had To Be - Music in Multiplayer Hangout
E's Jammy Jams - Soul and Mind - Music used during narration
Google Fonts - Fredoka One font used for signs
GIMP - Used for creating Multiplayer Hangout and other designs
Credits to @XShrunk for some ideas from their Getting Over It
Multiplayer project!
Check it out here: https://scratch.mit.edu/projects/390983761/
(I didn't use any of their scripts - I haven't even looked inside
of their project! - besides the main point of this project was for
me to learn how to make a multiplayer game)
- = - UPDATES - = -
- Players can no longer go onto the roof of the multiplayer
hangout. Seriously! Try to get up there! You can't!!
- Made it more clear if you're enabling or disabling player
collision when pressing G.
- [BUG FIX] Player collision is now enabled by default.
- [BUG FIX] Players can no longer jump in midair while
changing hats.
- Added the MULTIPLAYER HANGOUT! Hang out with your
friends and just chill out there!
- Added HATS! Use the [H] button to cycle through the hats
that you can wear.
- You can now listen to other players' SOUNDS! Sounds are
directional so you can hear if they're coming from the left
or the right!
- Added ability to push other players (using the [G] key will
disable this for you)
- TurboWarp is now officially supported! A Scratch account is
not needed to play on it, however names are randomly
generated.
- Forkphorus is not officially supported as there are still many
bugs, but you are still able to join if you want.
- You can now change what other people's names look like by
cycling through the options with the [V] key.
- The color of players are now affected by the time of day so the 1st
player isn't always the same color!
- Updated the title screen to make it look cooler!
- [BUG FIX] Pressing [T] to open the chat should now
automatically select the text input
- Added FOURTY more chat options!
- [IN BETA] Added spectator mode which will let you spectate
the game even if it's full (hold the spacebar when pressing
New Game)
- Fixed bug with sprite fencing
- Added auto AFK kicking system (you get kicked if you don't
move for 5 minutes)
- Added easy way to make someone the owner of the project
(add your username(s) to the game owners list)
- Added feature that will let owners kick all players when they
update the game.
- Gave owners crowns
- Added height traveled to nametags & added a counter in the
top left
- 2nd server assets implemented into the main project to make
it easier for me to update it
- Added support for EIGHT players!
- Added motion smoothing so other players aren't laggy
- Replaced Scratch Cat with rectangle dude so players would
look the same on everyone's screen
- Added Safe Chat
- Added offline detection
- Updated rectangle dude's sprite (added a cute face and made
it a littlebit taller)
- Fixed bug where players would flicker when on top of
another player
- Fixed bug where you could see old players for a second
when you joined
- Removed pause feature so players don't get treated as if
when they aren't
- Stopped the game from starting when connecting
